\frac{\left(1+\tan \left(x\right)\right)}{1-\tan \left(x\right)}=\frac{\cos \left(2x\right)}{1-\sin \left(2x\right)}
\cos x - \sin x
\frac{1+\tan x}{1-\tan x} = \frac{1+\frac{\sin x}{\cos x}}{1-\frac{\sin x}{\cos x}}      = \frac{\cos x + \sin x}{\cos x - \sin x}.
\frac{\cos x + \sin x}{\cos x - \sin x}      = \frac{\cos^2 x - \sin^2 x}{(\cos x-\sin x )^2}      = \frac{\cos 2x}{\cos^2 x + \sin^2 x - 2\sin x\cos x}      = \frac{\cos 2x}{1-\sin 2x}.
